title: WHIRLING F1 / HARDIE AFTER TALKING TO KLAASJE
description:
* Back from Klaasje.
* Get the doorgunner mixtape

dialogueTree.title: You: ""So I talked to Klaasje about the t..."
dialogueTree.text: "So I talked to Klaasje about the tape."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""And?""
links.text: "And?"

links.title: Composure: "He tenses immediately. Chest tighte..."
links.text: He tenses immediately. Chest tightens. Jaw sets. Ready for another blow.

links.title: You: ""And nothing. She stands by what sh..."
links.text: "And nothing. She stands by what she said."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""That fucking fucker..." He stares..."
links.text: "That fucking fucker..." He stares at his beer for two seconds -- intently -- then turns to you. "You're the worst cop in Revachol! I gave you *gold* on that tape."

links.title: Rhetoric: "That 'fucker' wasn't aimed at you...."
links.text: That 'fucker' wasn't aimed at you. It was at *her*.

links.title: Endurance: "You smell weakness. He's getting ti..."
links.text: You smell weakness. He's getting tired of the game he's been playing.

links.title: Savoir Faire: "You caught him off balance. Push an..."
links.text: You caught him off balance. Push and he will give way.

links.title: You: ""Gold? It was just locker room talk..."
links.text: "Gold? It was just locker room talk. It's not evidence."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""*Locker room talk*? What are you,..."
links.text: "*Locker room talk*? What are you, fucking brain-dead?! I've been to plenty of locker rooms -- they don't plan rapes there!"

links.title: Suggestion: "Sounds like he wanted it to change..."
links.text: Sounds like he wanted it to change her mind about the hanged man. This is definitely personal.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""What did she have to say then? Fin..."
links.text: "What did she have to say then? Fine by her?! This is what people are *supposed* to be like? Fucking whoopty doo!"

links.title: You: ""It was dark stuff, but it didn't p..."
links.text: "It was dark stuff, but it didn't prove anything. And it didn't change her mind."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Dark?! Dark is when you start a go..."
links.text: "Dark?! Dark is when you start a goddamn death-rock band! He said he'd rape her!" He shakes his head in disbelief.

links.title: You: ""Yeah it was bad. Honestly, I expec..."
links.text: "Yeah it was bad. Honestly, I expected it to have more effect..."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""No shit it was bad! The fuck did s..."
links.text: "No shit it was bad! The fuck did she say then? It's all *fuck-a-doodle-fine*? This is what people are supposed to talk like?!"

links.title: Suggestion: "Sounds like he wanted it to change..."
links.text: Sounds like he wanted it to change her mind about the hanged man. This is definitely personal.

links.title: You: ""She did not say it was *fuck-a-doo..."
links.text: "She did not say it was *fuck-a-doodle-fine*."

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can confirm that.""
links.text: "I can confirm that."

links.title: Esprit de Corps: "I see what you're doing there. Let'..."
links.text: I see what you're doing there. Let's push him.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""No *fuck-a-doodle-fine*? Oh, okay...."
links.text: "No *fuck-a-doodle-fine*? Oh, okay." He's too angry to find solace in his beer. "Well at least *that's* off the table then."

links.title: You: ""She did not say *whoopty doo*.""
links.text: "She did not say *whoopty doo*."

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can confirm that.""
links.text: "I can confirm that."

links.title: Esprit de Corps: "I see what you're doing there. Let'..."
links.text: I see what you're doing there. Let's push him.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""She didn't? Well, *whoopty doo* th..."
links.text: "She didn't? Well, *whoopty doo* then!" He's too angry to drink his beer. He just stares at it.

links.title: You: ""It did not come as a surprise to h..."
links.text: "It did not come as a surprise to her. And she definitely wasn't scared."

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. In fact..." The lieutenant lo..."
links.text: "Yes. In fact..." The lieutenant looks at you, then him. "I think she thought it was a little funny."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Funny?" Titus mumbles, his lips ba..."
links.text: "Funny?" Titus mumbles, his lips barely moving: "No good goddamn psycho whore..."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Right... right..." Titus mumbles,..."
links.text: "Right... right..." Titus mumbles, his lips barely moving: "No good goddamn psycho whore..."

links.title: Logic: "Seems like they wanted to give Klaa..."
links.text: Seems like they wanted to give Klaasje a second chance to play along -- she *still* didn't.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Alright!" He slams his giant fist..."
links.text: "Alright!" He slams his giant fist on the door frame. "All-fucking-righty then! I guess it's good then! That fucking..."

links.title: Elizabeth: ""Please try to control yourself in..."
links.text: "Please try to control yourself in the presence of *visitors*, Titus." Her voice is a bit softer than earlier.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""This is just perfect. Just fucking..."
links.text: "This is just perfect. Just fucking perfect. Any thoughts on this, lawman?" Titus rubs his chin with his palm, as if trying to grind it smooth.

links.title: Physical Instrument: "Women are crazy. Irrational. That's..."
links.text: Women are crazy. Irrational. That's what you're thinking, right? Also, your fists are itching for a bump.

links.title: Rhetoric: "No they're not. And you're not itch..."
links.text: No they're not. And you're not itching for any bumps. Don't betray your inexplicable feminist ideals for cheap macho friend-points.

links.title: Rhetoric: "You don't have to say everything ou..."
links.text: You don't have to say everything out loud. Just mix and match.

links.title: You: ""I think this is personal for you...."
links.text: "I think this is personal for you. I think you had feelings for her."

links.title: Glen: ""Pft!" Glen explodes with indignati..."
links.text: "Pft!" Glen explodes with indignation. "Everyone's got feelings for each other! Where are you going with this?!"

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""It's alright, Glen." He rubs his t..."
links.text: "It's alright, Glen." He rubs his temple. "I just thought she... I thought *anyone* would come around if they heard that shit. Apparently I was wrong."

links.title: Glen: ""Yeah, that was fucked up." He smil..."
links.text: "Yeah, that was fucked up." He smiles sympathetically.

links.title: Suggestion: "He wanted her to see the man for wh..."
links.text: He wanted her to see the man for what he was. Now that you know, you might wanna lay off this topic -- or else you might antagonize him.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""I just got too worked up. Big man..."
links.text: "I just got too worked up. Big man lost his shit." He shakes his head. "It's cool now."

links.title: You: ""I think you had a lie planned, but..."
links.text: "I think you had a lie planned, but she didn't play along."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""I asked for your opinion, not a be..."
links.text: "I asked for your opinion, not a bed-time story. Tell it to your grandma."

links.title: You: ""This tape was the last chance for..."
links.text: "This tape was the last chance for her to do what was planned."

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But she didn't. She knows she can'..."
links.text: "But she didn't. She knows she can't lie to us. Unlike you."

links.title: Volition: "Oh no... he's definitely compromise..."
links.text: Oh no... he's definitely compromised too. It's his *hubris*. Sadly not much to do about it now.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Fantastic. So *now* you remember h..."
links.text: "Fantastic. So *now* you remember how to do your job..." He despondently glances at his beer. "I'm so sick of this piss -- we should get something harder in here."

links.title: Shanky: ""Yeah, guys, we should get a party..."
links.text: "Yeah, guys, we should get a party going tonight!"

links.title: Theo: ""Why?""
links.text: "Why?"

links.title: Shanky: ""Uh..." He looks at the old man in..."
links.text: "Uh..." He looks at the old man in the corner. "Maybe not then."

links.title: Logic: "Success. They admitted to unlawful..."
links.text: Success. They admitted to unlawful collaboration to derail the investigation.

links.title: You: ""Sure, I'll do that.""
links.text: "Sure, I'll do that."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah, why don't you?" He's still d..."
links.text: "Yeah, why don't you?" He's still despondently looking at his beer.

links.title: You: ""You know what I think? Women are c..."
links.text: "You know what I think? Women are crazy, man."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""You can say that again, copper." H..."
links.text: "You can say that again, copper." He holds out his giant fist. "Right here."

links.title: Physical Instrument: "Here we go. Bump it hard."
links.text: Here we go. Bump it hard.

links.title: You: "Bump it."
links.text: Bump it.

links.title: Titus Hardie: "You fist connects with his. The sla..."
links.text: You fist connects with his. The slam isn't audible, because you did not bump it hard. Still, your knuckles tingle life-affirmingly.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""And now you, binoclard." His voice..."
links.text: "And now you, binoclard." His voice is chummy as he turns to the lieutenant.

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant adjusts his glasses,..."
links.text: The lieutenant adjusts his glasses, then extends his curled fist and taps Titus' bruised knuckles.

links.title: Esprit de Corps: "A bond has been formed."
links.text: A bond has been formed.

links.title: Physical Instrument: "Not bad."
links.text: Not bad.

links.title: You: "Bump it. Hard."
links.text: Bump it. Hard.

links.title: Titus Hardie: "Your fist connects with his. Hard...."
links.text: Your fist connects with his. Hard. The slam is audible. You can almost hear his bones ring. Your knuckles tingle life-affirmingly.

links.title: Pain Threshold: "A flash of pain, like slamming your..."
links.text: A flash of pain, like slamming your fist against iron. He is stronger than he looks -- and he looks like Ramout Karzai.

links.title: You: "Don't bump it."
links.text: Don't bump it.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""You just gonna leave a fella hangi..."
links.text: "You just gonna leave a fella hanging like that?" Titus shakes his head. "RCM queers..."

links.title: Glen: ""Yeah, they're all queers! Can't bu..."
links.text: "Yeah, they're all queers! Can't bump hard fist or anything."

links.title: Alain: ""Who are these people? To leave a f..."
links.text: "Who are these people? To leave a fella hanging like that..."

links.title: Physical Instrument: "What is wrong with you? You would h..."
links.text: What is wrong with you? You would have made friends for life! These guys will never forgive you now.

links.title: You: ""Maybe she isn't who you thought sh..."
links.text: "Maybe she isn't who you thought she was."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Nah... I know her." He looks upsta..."
links.text: "Nah... I know her." He looks upstairs, distracted. "She's just a girl in over her head."

links.title: You: ""Titus, she has my whole skill-set..."
links.text: "Titus, she has my whole skill-set compromised. She's some kind of a pro."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""What kind of pro? You're saying sh..."
links.text: "What kind of pro? You're saying she's a hooker?" He forces himself to pick up the beer and take a gulp.

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No, he's not saying that. Forget a..."
links.text: "No, he's not saying that. Forget about it."

links.title: Shanky: ""She's not a hooker. I know hookers..."
links.text: "She's not a hooker. I know hookers." He thinks for a moment. "She's more like an escort or a...."

links.title: Eugene: ""Shut the fuck up, Shanky.""
links.text: "Shut the fuck up, Shanky."

links.title: You: ""You don't know?! She's a model! Sh..."
links.text: "You don't know?! She's a model! She won a pageant!"

links.title: Glen: ""I knew it! Titus, I knew she was p..."
links.text: "I knew it! Titus, I knew she was professionally trained -- by her walk!" Glen seems excited. "I told you she was a beauty queen!"

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Yes, Glen." Titus pinches the root..."
links.text: "Yes, Glen." Titus pinches the root of his nose. "I know she's a beauty queen. Everyone can see that."

links.title: Glen: ""Sorry." Glen settles down."
links.text: "Sorry." Glen settles down.

links.title: You: ""Titus, she has special training. A..."
links.text: "Titus, she has special training. And I'm not talking about Oranjese lit."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""I don't know what the fuck that me..."
links.text: "I don't know what the fuck that means. Oranjese lit? What is that shit? Literature?"

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I've noticed the same." The lieute..."
links.text: "I've noticed the same." The lieutenant says to you quickly, then turns to Titus: "Yes. He meant Oranjese literature. Women are always reading, right?"

links.title: Esprit de Corps: "The lieutenant adjusts his electron..."
links.text: The lieutenant adjusts his electronic wristwatch. Psychological and physical training from an unknown government body. I noticed it. You noticed it. They haven't.

links.title: Alain: ""Don't worry, Titus, we know her. B..."
links.text: "Don't worry, Titus, we know her. Besides, you know how it is with bitches and books."

links.title: You: ""Titus, she has special training. A..."
links.text: "Titus, she has special training. And I'm not talking about self-defence lessons."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Special like what? Like a professi..."
links.text: "Special like what? Like a professional dancer? Or..." He squints at you. "Are you trying to tell me she's a stripper?"

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I've noticed the same." The lieute..."
links.text: "I've noticed the same." The lieutenant says to you quickly, then turns to Titus: "Yes. He meant a professional dancer. Women are always dancing, right?"

links.title: Esprit de Corps: "The lieutenant adjusts his electron..."
links.text: The lieutenant adjusts his electronic wristwatch. Psychological and physical training from an unknown government body. I noticed it. You noticed it. They haven't.

links.title: Alain: ""Don't worry, Titus, we know her. B..."
links.text: "Don't worry, Titus, we know her. Besides, you know how it is with bitches and dances."

links.title: You: ""She's not some helpless girl. She..."
links.text: "She's not some helpless girl. She handled the mercenary well enough."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""*Handled* him?" He baulks. "She go..."
links.text: "*Handled* him?" He baulks. "She got into some stupid shit with that guy. Shit *we* had to take care of."

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, yes, we heard all about it an..."
links.text: "Yes, yes, we heard all about it and the fact still stands: you were more disturbed by the tape than her."

links.title: You: ""She's a hard-core party girl with..."
links.text: "She's a hard-core party girl with a bigger death wish than mine."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah..." He cracks his knuckles th..."
links.text: "Yeah..." He cracks his knuckles thoughtfully. "You're right about that -- she takes *way* too many drugs."

links.title: Alain: ""Well, it's as they say -- you can'..."
links.text: "Well, it's as they say -- you can't do anything with an *underdose*," the Mesque says with a philosophical look in his eyes.

links.title: Electrochemistry: "With an overdose you can at least t..."
links.text: With an overdose you can at least try to come off it. Take a bath, do breathing exercises, get medical attention as necessary. With an underdose you're just *you*.

links.title: Rhetoric: "Yeah... *underdose* isn't an actual..."
links.text: Yeah... *underdose* isn't an actual word.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah, but I mean -- she has an act..."
links.text: "Yeah, but I mean -- she has an actual drug problem. Not like you. Not like us." He glances at his beer. "I don't think I've ever seen her sober."

links.title: You: ""Huh, I guess you do know her then.""
links.text: "Huh, I guess you do know her then."

links.title: Shanky: ""Yeah, he fucking told you he knows..."
links.text: "Yeah, he fucking told you he knows her!"

links.title: You: ""Maybe she is still in denial. You..."
links.text: "Maybe she is still in denial. You know, like a defence mechanism."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah... maybe. That is a possibili..."
links.text: "Yeah... maybe. That is a possibility."

links.title: Suggestion: "He does not sound very convinced an..."
links.text: He does not sound very convinced anymore.

links.title: You: ""Be straight with me, Titus: What r..."
links.text: "Be straight with me, Titus: What really happened?" (Wrap this up.)

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""I already told you." He puts his g..."
links.text: "I already told you." He puts his giant face in his hands and sighs. "We fucking hanged him."

links.title: Empathy: "There's less gusto in his voice now..."
links.text: There's less gusto in his voice now. His men too are growing increasingly silent.

links.title: Drama: "They're confused. This is growing o..."
links.text: They're confused. This is growing over their heads.

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""C'mon, Titus. We know you didn't h..."
links.text: "C'mon, Titus. We know you didn't hang him. He was *shot*." He taps on his notebook. "I know you're tired; so am I -- why don't you just..."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""You know what?" He gets closer. "I..."
links.text: "You know what?" He gets closer. "I *am* tired. I'm tired of you *and* the whore upstairs."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Next time you see her -- tell her..."
links.text: "Next time you see her -- tell her Titus said FUCK OFF!" He throws his beer can down.

links.title: Half Light: "This is the petulant rage of someon..."
links.text: This is the petulant rage of someone who's at the end of their wits.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""That lying, scamming... We're done..."
links.text: "That lying, scamming... We're done! This is over, you understand? Your little investigation -- is OVER."

links.title: Alain: ""Yeah..." There is a silence in the..."
links.text: "Yeah..." There is a silence in the room. Alain starts saying something -- then thinks best not to.

links.title: Perception (Sight): "On the floor, beer drips out of the..."
links.text: On the floor, beer drips out of the can, into a small puddle. No one does anything about it.

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""What is this quiet funeral shit? W..."
links.text: "What is this quiet funeral shit? What we need is some *beers* in us!" He looks around. "BARTENDER! Twenty beers for the Dockworkers' Union!"

links.title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Why don't we make it FORTY, huh?"..."
links.text: "Why don't we make it FORTY, huh?" The man shouts from behind the counter. "Why don't we make it A HUNDRED beers, you're not loud enough!"

links.title: Glen: ""A hundred beers -- now we're talki..."
links.text: "A hundred beers -- now we're talking!" Glen livens up. "Hoppity-hop over here cafeteria manager!"

links.title: Electrochemistry: "The window might be closing. The mo..."
links.text: The window might be closing. The more beers they get in them, the less cooperative they will be.

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""C'mon, Titus. The stakes are too h..."
links.text: "C'mon, Titus. The stakes are too high here. There will be blood on the streets -- the tribunal, remember?" He closes his notebook. "I know you're tired -- why don't you just..."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""You know what?" He gets closer. "I..."
links.text: "You know what?" He gets closer. "I *am* tired. I'm tired of you, them *and* the whore upstairs."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Next time you see her -- tell her..."
links.text: "Next time you see her -- tell her Titus said FUCK OFF!" He throws his beer can down.

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""C'mon, Titus, it's been a long day..."
links.text: "C'mon, Titus, it's been a long day. I'm tired of running back and forth between you. I can see you're tired too -- why don't you just..."

links.title: Reaction Speed: "The man is slowing down. Looks like..."
links.text: The man is slowing down. Looks like a bad blood sugar crash. He can't keep track of all the variables anymore.

links.title: Drama: "Who could? It's getting harder and..."
links.text: Who could? It's getting harder and harder to perform one's part in this sordid play. All it takes is a nudge...

links.title: You: ""Actually, I think it made her a li..."
links.text: "Actually, I think it made her a little *nostalgic*."

links.title: You: ""If anything, she seemed turned on..."
links.text: "If anything, she seemed turned on by the whole doorgunning thing."

links.title: You: ""The Doorgunner Megamix scared you..."
links.text: "The Doorgunner Megamix scared you more than it did her -- you need to accept that."

links.title: Glen: ""Scared us?! It didn't scare fuckin..."
links.text: "Scared us?! It didn't scare fucking anyone!" The blond looks like he's about to jump up, but then settles down. "Titus, I'm fucking confused here."

links.title: You: ""Titus, she said she would like to..."
links.text: "Titus, she said she would like to be a little doorgunner herself, if she could."

links.title: You: ""She pretty much laughed it off, Ti..."
links.text: "She pretty much laughed it off, Titus."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""Fucking fuckedy fucker!" He shakes..."
links.text: "Fucking fuckedy fucker!" He shakes his head in disbelief. "And what did she say then? That it's fine?! People are *supposed* to be like that?!"

links.title: You: ""I'll get back to you on that one.""
links.text: "I'll get back to you on that one."

links.title: Titus Hardie: ""The fuck do you mean *you'll get b..."
links.text: "The fuck do you mean *you'll get back to me*?!" he roars. "NO! Tell me she said she was raped!"

links.title: Half Light: "He completely blew his fuse there...."
links.text: He completely blew his fuse there. The calm act is completely gone.

links.title: You: ""She didn't say that.""
links.text: "She didn't say that."

links.title: You: ""I said I'll get back to you." [Lea..."
links.text: "I said I'll get back to you." [Leave.]
